        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 8:26PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 826 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Saxe, or 7 miles southwest of Charlotte Court House, moving east at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Keysville...
Charlotte Court House...
Phenix...
Drakes Branch...
Madisonville...
Abilene...
and Cullen.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
central Virginia.</instruction>
